description:
&lt;p&gt;Twilight Porter / Driver / Security . Part time. Fixed term vacancies at Chorley Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So many people want to join us to work as a Porter – the things is, we don’t want just anyone, we want the very best. As a Porter, you play such an invaluable role supporting the day to day running of our hospitals transporting patients, equipment, medication, samples, test results from one location to another, all with a smile on your face. This is why we don’t compromise when it comes to choosing new colleagues to join us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We need people with fabulous customer services skills who are passionate in working to their very best to deliver services right across our hospitals. You will help directly with supporting patients move to different parts of the hospital, often when they are at their most scared. Your reassuring and friendly demeanour can really make the difference to their experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As well as transferring patients throughout the site, in your very familiar and recognisable porters uniform, you will deliver laundry, internal mail, collect clinical/domestic waste, you will attend fire and security alerts, as well as quickly grab the crash trolley when needed for cardiac arrests…in fact, there is no part of the hospital you won’t support. Getting your 10,000 steps a day in will be a doddle for you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will be a fantastic team worker, who has experience of working with colleagues in a busy environment and also has basic computer skills. The world has gone digital so these skills are becoming more and more important.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;There isn’t another role like this around – so it goes without saying that full training will be given which will include all aspects of portering duties - we know you will proudly wear the uniform provided and join a team of over 150 colleagues from all backgrounds who work together to keep the hospital ticking smoothly..we asked our team why they enjoyed their role and this quote really resonated with us:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;“I love my job, it gives me a great deal of satisfaction. I don’t need to work here – I choose to.”&lt;br /&gt;You will feel really proud to join our team, doing your bit for the NHS at this really difficult time in our history. There is so much love for us at the moment, rainbows everywhere to show support from the public – so joining us at this time really will make an impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Our services run 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, 365 days a year. If you are needed at any point during the day or night, hospital staff contact the main office with their request. These requests could vary from taking blood to Pathology to assisting in a cardiac arrest on a ward…..so we genuinely mean it when we say that no two days are the same.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSteven JonesJob titlePortering Services ManagerEmail addresssteven.JONES@lthtr.nhs.ukTelephone number01257 245235Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These exciting job roles based at Chorley and District General Hospital are what we call, Twilight Porters and you will be supporting mainly our E&amp;D but also all our other wards and departments. This is a direct patient position and there are two vacancies working 5 hours shifts from late evening in to the early hours of the morning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shift times to be confirmed but some flexibility is required due to service demands.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Position 1. Working Sunday, Monday, Tuesday and Wednesday. 5 hours each shift = 20 hours&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Position 2. Working Thursday - Friday - Saturday. Working 5 hours each shift = 15 hours&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full training will be given along with a Trust uniform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These roles are on a fixed term contract until the end of March 2021.&lt;/p&gt;
